{
  "texts": [
    "This led to a systematic study of the consistency of variational approximation via PAC-Bayes bounds (Alquier et al., 2016; Sheth and Khardon, 2017).",
    "• on the other hand, little was known at that time on the theoretical properties of variational approximations of the posterior in statistics.",
    "Using the fact that variational approximations of tempered posteriors are constrained minimizers of the PAC-Bayes bound of Bhattacharya et al. (2019), we studied the consistency of such approximations (Alquier and Ridgway, 2020).",
    "As a byproduct we have a generalization of the prior mass condition for variational inference (Alquier and Ridgway, 2020, (2.1) and (2.2)).",
    "These results were extended to the standard posterior π(dθ|X 1,."
  ]
}